																								 New Delhi, Nov. 13: Six key infrastructure industries grew by a disappointing 6 per cent in September this year against 10.6 per cent a year ago. The growth during April-September also dropped to 6.6 per cent from 8.7 per cent in the corresponding period of the previous year. Crude petroleum production put up the worst performance with a negative growth of 0.7 per cent against 9.4 per cent a year ago.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 13: Reliance Energy Ltd (REL) has been allocated two coal blocks in Orissa jointly with five other companies. The government allocated the Rampia and dip side of Rampia coal blocks. The allocation will help REL set up a power generation capacity of 1,000MW.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 13: Commerce and industry minister Kamal Nath has written to Prime Minister Manmohan Singh seeking a larger discussion on the issue of spectrum allocation. Nath said the battle between the government and GSM players may affect the investment environment and deter overseas players.																								 Tehran, Nov. 13: Iran has given India a four-month deadline to agree to participate in a multi-billion dollar project to transport Iranian gas to India via Pakistan.
